    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of May 24 article on Rep Rick A Lazio Senate campaign appearance on subway; cheapest MetroCard costs $1.50</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article yesterday about Representative Rick A. Lazio and his campaign appearance on the No. 6 subway line misstated the price of a MetroCard. While Mr. Lazio said it was about $3 and the article said the cheapest card was $4, both answers were wrong. Station vending machines sell a card for $1.50, good for one ride.</p>
      </block>
